<section id="what-is" class="guide-section">
    <h2>What Is an <span class="gradient-text">AI Automation Stack</span>?</h2>
    <p>An <strong>AI automation stack</strong> is a curated collection of tools, models, and workflows that work together to automate repetitive tasks, amplify human decision-making, and scale output without scaling headcount.</p>
    <p>Unlike a single AI tool doing isolated tasks, a stack is <strong>systematic</strong> — each layer feeds into the next, creating a flywheel of efficiency:</p>
    <pre>Input → AI Processing → Automated Workflow → Output → Analytics → Optimization → Repeat</pre>
    <div class="callout">
        <h4>Why 2026 Is the Year to Build Your Stack</h4>
        <ul>
            <li>AI tool maturity has crossed the "actually useful" threshold</li>
            <li>Integration between tools has dramatically improved</li>
            <li>Costs have dropped 10–100x compared to 2024</li>
            <li>Open-source alternatives now rival commercial products in many areas</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</section>

