<!-- SECTION 10: Pitfalls -->
<section id="pitfalls" class="guide-section">
    <h2>Common <span class="gradient-text">Pitfalls</span> & How to Avoid Them</h2>
    <ol style="color: #94a3b8; padding-left: 24px;">
        <li><strong style="color:#e2e8f0;">Tool Hoarding</strong> — Start with 3–5 essential tools. Add more only when a clear need emerges.</li>
        <li><strong style="color:#e2e8f0;">Over-Automation</strong> — Keep customer-critical touchpoints human. Automate repetitive tasks, not relationships.</li>
        <li><strong style="color:#e2e8f0;">No Measurement</strong> — Define success metrics for each tool before implementing. Review monthly.</li>
        <li><strong style="color:#e2e8f0;">Ignoring Integration Costs</strong> — Budget 4–8 hours for initial setup of each major tool.</li>
        <li><strong style="color:#e2e8f0;">Skipping the "Why"</strong> — Document the specific problem before choosing a solution.</li>
    </ol>
</section>

